Notes: Really fun! Crux beta I landed on was reach left to arete pinch, frog feet on arete, match in on right crimp above the pinch, big move up to jug, clip shake, then right crimp, left crimp, left heel hook on arete horn, right hand to jug, clip, then left hand arete, bump left to undercling, get opposing high left foot, step up right foot, then hit right pinch jug. Pumpy af for such a short route, fun stuff.

Notes:
Puzzling out the crux, beta I settled on: 
Left hand side pull top of hold, stand up into the lh undercling and deadpoint to right crimp. Bump right to sidpull, high left foot back step right under the start hold of boulder, release left hand and go to sloper, bump to crimp. High right foot on prev crimp, bump right hand to sloper, left hand to jug. Left foot tucked under on edges, heel hook right sidepull, bump right hand again to divot in high sloper, sort feet and throw right hand to finish jug. Fun climb!
